			<notes/>
			<notesNormalized/>
			<notesHtml/>
			<text>Key Facts
A recent index of 301 diseases found mental health problems to be one of the main causes of the overall disease burden worldwide.(They were shown to account for 21.2% of years lived with disability worldwide) (1).

In 2015, common mental health problems (e.g. anxiety, depression and stress) and more serious mental health problems were the third most important cause of sick leave. In 2015, mental-health-related issues were found to lead to approximately 17.6 million days’ sick leave, or 12.7% of the total sick days taken in the UK (2)

Substantial treatment gap: 75% untreated (3)

Early death: 15-20 years premature mortality for those with severe mental illness</text>
		</slide>
